eNCA's Senior reporter Ayesha Ismail has the details. #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The bail application of Zandile Christmas Mafe has been postponed to 29 January. Mafe is still in isolation, after contracting COVID-19. The state, Defence and the Acting President of the Regional Court met to discuss logistics on Friday. READ: Order to send Zandile Mafe to psychiatric hospital set aside They agreed to postpone as the defence can't consult until Mafe is out of isolation on Monday. He was released from Valkenberg Psychiatric Hospital after the defence applied for a review of his referral. Mafe is currently in custody at Pollsmoor Prison.